<Base title="UX Testing" description="UX testing – evaluating the functionality of your online shop by Hob by Horse.">
<div class="lp"><section class="hero"><div class="hi">
<p class="kicker">Strategy</p>
<h1>UX Testing – Evaluating the Functionality of Your Online Shop</h1>
<p>In UX testing, we take a close look at the current applications and services of your online shop. We want to find out how the shopping experience for your target groups is shaped at the current front end. We then develop any improvements needed, tailored to your business model using Shopware 6 and our know-how from years of development experience in e-commerce.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Definition of UX Testing and Optimisation Offers by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>UX testing replays visits to your online shop from the user's perspective. We evaluate with an unbiased view as theoretical outsiders: how fast the website loads, which action options we can use at what speed, and in what sensible ratio the page layout and dynamic page elements are placed in relation to each other. In the best case, we find weaknesses that we can fix immediately.</p>
<h2>Test Steps for Practically Relevant UX Testing</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Define test goals:</strong> Do you want to redesign, remodel, expand or upgrade your online shop? The test provides indications for specific improvement needs.</li>
<li><strong>Choose method and create prototype:</strong> Where and according to what pattern should the UX test take place? We create a prototype that is as functional as you wish for the customers of your business model.</li>
<li><strong>Recruit test persons:</strong> These real shop visitors ideally come from your target group in your market segment or market niche. When assembling, it is best to consider mixed groups following the persona example.</li>
<li><strong>Conduct UX testing:</strong> Do you want to conduct a moderated or unmoderated UX test? A moderator is present in both cases; in the unmoderated test, the test result is documented in writing for later reviews and analyses. Additional feedback from test persons individually and/or as a test group is also helpful.</li>
<li><strong>Collect and evaluate test results:</strong> For data evaluation, we work according to quantitative and qualitative measurement methods. Helpful are surveys, tracking software for user behaviour (eye movements, mouse movements), discussion rounds or a list of problems identified by users.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Specifying UX Testing for Industries</h2>
<p>Groups for UX testing come from the food industry, wholesale and automotive industry, or fashion and lifestyle. The expectations and reactions of service providers from the insurance, real estate and tourism sectors are also exciting. On a small scale, the effort of tests is also worthwhile for business models in all craft sectors, with artists and art dealers, as well as authorities and institutions from politics, science, research and development.</p>
<h2>UX Testing by Hob by Horse According to Target Groups</h2>
<p>UX testing assumes a certain familiar behaviour from B2B target groups when using online shops. Where these test groups stumble over hurdles, you can efficiently improve. B2C additionally involves dependence on short-term or emerging longer-term trends. Every constellation of digital commerce can be assembled with this tool to optimise shopping experiences for your target group.</p>
<p><em>Would you like to use UX testing to determine the current functionality of your online shop? Arrange a consultation appointment with Hob by Horse by <a href="mailto:info@hob-by-horse.de">email</a> or telephone!</em></p>
</div></div>
